description:
&lt;p&gt;The Community Hospital Senior Matron will play a key role in the leadership of the Community Hospital Teams as part of the management team and will support the Intermediate Care Services, Senior Manager, to ensure the delivery of quality care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;They will take accountability for the delivery of the highest standards of nursing practice and clinical care delivered to patients within the community hospital settings across NWS, working in partnership with Adult Social Care teams and key stakeholders. To secure and aspire to the highest standards of clinical care by providing leadership to Multi Professional Teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be expected to work across 7 days with clinical leadership responsibilities, and participate in the Senior Clinician on Call Rota.&lt;/p&gt;
